112
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:32,120
Besides,

113
00:05:32,490 --> 00:05:38,070
I hope this training can help you gain some good awareness.

114
00:05:39,190 --> 00:05:41,450
Let's take a look at the materials first.

115
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:42,920
Sakawa.

116
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:44,100
Sakawa.

117
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:44,690
Yes.

118
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:46,310
Do it faster.

119
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:47,380
Got it.

120
00:05:48,690 --> 00:05:50,480
Communication can be done

121
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,110
through multiple approaches according to

122
00:05:52,110 --> 00:05:54,930
the degree of hearing impairment of the other party and the environment.

123
00:05:54,930 --> 00:05:57,780
We need to find out which approach the other party wants to take the most

124
00:05:57,780 --> 00:06:01,040
and take corresponding measures. This is very important.

125
00:06:06,010 --> 00:06:09,740
Some elders may not be able to hear you when you talk to him like this.

126
00:06:10,010 --> 00:06:12,300
Therefore, we should enter their sight

127
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:15,970
and give them a signal with hand gestures like this.

128
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:16,890
Besides,

129
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:21,240
gently tapping the other party's shoulder to attract attention

130
00:06:21,460 --> 00:06:23,030
is another approach.

131
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:23,930
Now,

132
00:06:24,090 --> 00:06:26,290
although you're here,

133
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:27,130
the company

134
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,490
is still paying you salary.

135
00:06:30,030 --> 00:06:33,830
As a social being, please don't forget that it's still working time.

136
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:37,280
Let's carry on.

137
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:39,310
What's your emergency?

138
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:41,960
Emergency. One more time.

139
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:44,080
What is

140
00:06:44,730 --> 00:06:45,990
