189
00:09:11,370 --> 00:09:12,150
Well,

190
00:09:13,050 --> 00:09:13,690
yes.

191
00:09:14,190 --> 00:09:16,590
Although I said you were being idealistic,

192
00:09:19,190 --> 00:09:22,250
ideals are what everyone wants to pursue.

193
00:09:23,770 --> 00:09:24,410
Hehe.

194
00:09:25,570 --> 00:09:29,370
That's why I wanted to work with you, a person who pursues his ideals.

195
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:33,540
Our company also hopes that one day,

196
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:36,560
we can provide more services besides sign language.

197
00:09:36,950 --> 00:09:38,720
No matter how hard it is,

198
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:41,120
it'll be lame to give up easily.

199
00:09:44,170 --> 00:09:45,680
What you said

200
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:49,160
is for us to turn into an international design company, right?

201
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:54,980
Well,

202
00:09:57,490 --> 00:09:59,020
to achieve those is also why

203
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,990
I wanted to work here.

204
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:01,550
Yes.

205
00:10:03,910 --> 00:10:04,600
But

206
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,410
if it goes on like this,

207
00:10:08,820 --> 00:10:10,950
I feel I'm like a jack-of-all-trades.

208
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:14,180
I'm

209
00:10:15,430 --> 00:10:16,920
not like those around me.

210
00:10:17,810 --> 00:10:20,070
Some want to be social insurance agents,

211
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:22,420
and some want to be movie directors.

212
00:10:23,470 --> 00:10:26,070
