00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:55,340
Just come.

292
00:15:55,370 --> 00:15:57,010
There will be many people next time.

293
00:15:57,010 --> 00:15:57,790
You have a lot of friends, don't you?

294
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,450
-Are you asking me out?
-Yeah.

295
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:00,380
Hi, Taichi.

296
00:16:00,780 --> 00:16:01,360
Taichi?

297
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:07,560
Looks like something happened to him.

298
00:16:07,670 --> 00:16:13,160
Well, as for the suitable note-taker for you, Sugihara,

299
00:16:14,660 --> 00:16:17,790
I think you should pick someone from the Law Department.

300
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:24,190
Sugihara?

301
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:27,840
Yes.

302
00:16:34,170 --> 00:16:37,370
All right, I'll find you someone from the Law Department.

303
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:56,960
I'm home.

304
00:16:58,630 --> 00:16:59,510
You're back.

305
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,720
Hey, Grandpa.

306
00:17:06,349 --> 00:17:07,230
Yes?

307
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:11,890
What do you think if I say I want to drop out of college?

308
00:17:13,829 --> 00:17:15,230
It's fine by me.

309
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:16,960
What?

310
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:19,500
I mean, do whatever you want.

311
00:17:19,930 --> 00:17:20,599
Huh?

312
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:23,280
You're not stopping me? And you are not angry?

313
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:26,700
Is the reason why you want to drop out something I should be mad about?

314
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:27,970
No, of course not.

315
00:17:29,210 --> 00:17:32,210
You're going to school with the money you make anyway.

316
00:17:33,350 --> 00:17:35,090
Do whatever you want.

317
00:17:36,410 --> 00:17:37,230
But

318
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:40,210
I'm still being too willful, aren't I?

319
00:17:40,730 --> 00:17:41,450
What?

320
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:45,570
I finally have a friend who trusts me so much,

321
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:48,780
but I'm being capricious for my own reasons.

322
00:17:49,020 --> 00:17:49,930
Why?

323
00:17:50,610 --> 00:17:53,290
Did you have a fight with your friend for that?

324
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:56,130
You and that friend of yours

325
00:17:56,780 --> 00:17:59,180
will graduate in two or three years anyway.

326
00:17:59,580 --> 00:18:01,710
You'll still have to say goodbye then.

327
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:05,340
You're not middle school students anymore.

328
00:18:05,490 --> 00:18:07,310
Why are you acting like a baby?

329
00:18:07,510 --> 00:18:08,880
I'm not!

330
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:10,800
No matter who he is,

331
00:18:11,330 --> 00:18:12,500
you can't

332
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:15,870
stay in a place with him forever.

333
00:18:17,890 --> 00:18:21,170
You're actually the easiest to feel lonely.

334
00:18:22,790 --> 00:18:25,160
You always act like a child.

335
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:27,470
Who are you talking about, old man?

336
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,100
You are exactly

337
00:18:34,610 --> 00:18:37,170
like my stupid son in this regard.

338
00:18:46,740 --> 00:18:48,030
Hey, Taichi.

339
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:52,510
When you need to make a choice,

340
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:57,550
don't take loneliness into consideration.

341
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:00,500
As humans,

342
00:19:01,170 --> 00:19:02,300
when we feel lonely,

343
00:19:03,690 --> 00:19:06,690
we won't be able to see the path under our feet clearly.

344
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:08,430
That way,

345
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:11,330
we'll end up taking the wrong path.

346
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:13,950
You should

347
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:16,360
light up the path under your feet

348
00:19:17,020 --> 00:19:18,420
and choose a bright path.

349
00:19:20,370 --> 00:19:20,970
All right?

350
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:41,540
Maya.

351
00:19:42,820 --> 00:19:43,880
How was your class?

352
00:19:44,190 --> 00:19:46,530
Did you get along well with your note-taker?

353
00:19:46,530 --> 00:19:47,460
Well...

354
00:19:48,130 --> 00:19:48,860
Pretty well.

355
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,230
Will everything go well for me?

356
00:19:53,870 --> 00:19:54,360
Yes?

357
00:19:55,150 --> 00:19:57,010
Be with someone who's not Taichi.

358
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:04,110
Maya?

359
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:16,880
Well...

360
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:19,810
Senior,

361
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:23,660
do you like that guy?

362
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:32,170
Yes.

363
00:20:34,970 --> 00:20:36,830
But it's just my unrequited love.

364
00:20:38,620 --> 00:20:40,150
You're really sharp, Maya.

365
00:20:41,630 --> 00:20:44,010
-Or am I just too easy to see through?
-Hey.

366
00:20:48,670 --> 00:20:50,990
Why does it have to be him?

367
00:20:55,140 --> 00:20:56,410
He's so rude

368
00:20:57,350 --> 00:20:58,330
and naive.

369
00:20:59,290 --> 00:21:03,220
It may look like he's helping you, but he's always causing you trouble.

370
00:21:04,630 --> 00:21:07,140
Do you really need him?

371
00:21:17,310 --> 00:21:18,190
Maya.

372
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:21,180
Have you ever hoped

373
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:24,060
that your ears are not like this?

374
00:21:26,330 --> 00:21:26,820
What?

375
00:21:29,690 --> 00:21:30,460
I have.

376
00:21:34,110 --> 00:21:35,770
I wished countless times that

377
00:21:39,650 --> 00:21:41,050
I could hear clearly.

378
00:21:42,290 --> 00:21:45,020
That way, my life might be completely different.

379
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:50,180
I may not be afraid of talking,

380
00:21:51,410 --> 00:21:53,740
and I may not have to force smiles anymore.

381
00:21:54,190 --> 00:21:56,720
I may challenge new things one after another.

382
00:21:57,520 --> 00:22:00,320
And there may be many things that can make me happy.

383
00:22:02,310 --> 00:22:04,840
But I dropped that kind of thought a while ago.

384
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:08,090
No matter I was happy

385
00:22:08,320 --> 00:22:09,440
or mad,

386
00:22:10,410 --> 00:22:13,370
I wanted to do something for someone.

387
00:22:18,050 --> 00:22:19,330
I wanted to live on

388
00:22:21,080 --> 00:22:22,680
without thinking anything.

389
00:22:26,820 --> 00:22:27,400
But

390
00:22:30,370 --> 00:22:31,730
when I was with Taichi,

391
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:33,750
I remembered it all over again.

392
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:39,600
He's always hungry.

393
00:22:41,430 --> 00:22:45,490
For someone else's sake, he'd get even angrier than the person involved.

394
00:22:49,450 --> 00:22:51,640
He'd try harder to tell me every joke the professor told

395
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:54,270
rather than the content of class itself.

396
00:23:01,350 --> 00:23:04,880
When I realized it, I found I already started laughing with him.

397
00:23:08,950 --> 00:23:10,680
I'm so lucky to have met Taichi.

398
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:16,850
Ever since I met Taichi,

399
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:21,640
I've been feeling that I can stay the way I am now.

400
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:33,440
Although there are still many undelightful things,

401
00:23:40,030 --> 00:23:41,290
and although I thought

402
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:44,460
I didn't want this kind of ears countless times,

403
00:23:47,310 --> 00:23:48,640
ever since I met Taichi,

404
00:23:52,260 --> 00:23:54,860
I've been feeling it's good to stay the way I am.

405
00:24:00,710 --> 00:24:01,360
So,

406
00:24:03,350 --> 00:24:04,690
I hope

407
00:24:07,190 --> 00:24:08,990
I could have more time like this.

408
00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:34,380
Excuse me.

409
00:24:36,220 --> 00:24:39,280
I'm here to go through the procedures for dropping out.

410
00:24:40,610 --> 00:24:41,230
What?

411
00:24:46,730 --> 00:24:48,230
Do you have time tonight?

412
00:24:46,910 --> 00:24:51,770
[In the Next Episode]

413
00:24:48,260 --> 00:24:49,960
I have something to tell you.

414
00:24:50,090 --> 00:24:52,160
You've worked hard enough.

415
00:24:52,180 --> 00:24:54,590
Even the tiniest things that no one would notice

416
00:24:54,590 --> 00:24:56,100
can't escape your eyes.

417
00:24:56,220 --> 00:24:57,030
Do you know

418
00:24:57,150 --> 00:25:01,700
[This drama is purely fictional. The names of all characters and groups in this drama are fictional.]

419
00:24:57,340 --> 00:24:59,090
how happy I am for that?

420
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:01,380
Thank you for taking notes for me.
